1. Check if you are connected to Lighting network. Please refer to this knowledge article [How to connect to the Lighting WiFi network (LIGHTING) on Windows 10](https://signify.service-now.com/kb_view.do?sysparm_article=KB00059993)
2. Check if you have Global Print Cirrato client installed. Please refer to this knowledge article [How can you install the Global Print Cirrato client if it is missing?](https://signify.service-now.com/kb_view.do?sysparm_article=KB00114852) 
3. Check if your Print badge is registered in the Lighting (LUX) domain for access to Global Print Cirrato “Follow you” Printing/Copying. Please refer to this knowledge article [“Global Print Cirrato Badge Registration Process”](https://signify.service-now.com/kb_view.do?sysparm_article=KB00027667)
4. Check this knowledge article  [How can I use Global Print Follow You printing at the Philips Lighting site I am visiting?](https://signify.service-now.com/kb_view.do?sysparm_article=KB00114856)
